quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  4,135,"O you who have attained faith, always stand for justice, as witnesses for the sake of Allah, even if against yourselves or the parents or the close relatives. Whether a person is rich or poor, Allah is worthier as a patron of both. So do not follow prejudice{1}so as to do justice. But if you twist(your testimony){2}or disregard<i>(giving it) </i>—then indeed Allah has always been All-Aware of what you do.",footnotes:1:[Literally, ‘whim’.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Ibn Amer and Hamza read it as: “But whether you go forward (by testifying) or disregard…”]
  4,136,"O you who have attained faith, have faith in Allah and His Messenger and the Scripture which Hebestowed{1}upon His Messenger from on high and the Scripture He sent down before. And whoever denies Allah and His angels and His books and His messengers and the Last Day, then he has surely strayed into extreme misguidance.",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Ibn Amer read it as: “…and the Scripture which was bestowed upon…”
  4,137,"Indeed, those who attained faith then denied, then attained faith then denied, then increased in denial—never is Allah to forgive them nor guide them to a way."
  4,138,"Give<sup>sg </sup>glad tidings{1}to the hypocrites that they will have a painful punishment—",footnotes:1:This is said in sarcasm.
  4,139,"those who take the deniers as allies apart from the believers. Do they seek might from them? For indeed, all might belongs to Allah."
  4,140,"ForHe has surely bestowed{1}upon you<sup>pl </sup>from on high, in the Scripture, that when you hear Allah’s signs being denied or ridiculed, then do not sit with them until they engage in some other discourse; you would then be like them. Indeed, Allah will gather the hypocrites and the deniers in Hell, all together—",footnotes:1:Qira’at: All except for Asem and Ya’qub read it as: “For it has surely been bestowed upon you….”
